  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research evaluating hemolysis risk in centrifugal blood pump designs. The CFD hemolysis prediction framework for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was assessed under ventricular assist device operating conditions. All thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were reviewed; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps consistent with Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across blood viscosity, pump speed, and inlet flow boundary conditions. Despite gaps in several credibility factors, the overall evidence package was judged sufficient for the intended low-risk regulatory submission pathway, and the decision record reflects acceptance. No structured Context of Use object is bound to this assurance unit; the intended-use scope is conveyed only through the narrative above.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-2021",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-2022"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
